Edecan FyDesign Engine
Copyright 2026 Edecan contributors

This package contains a security-reviewed, clean distribution of the FyDesign
creative runtime, contributed by its copyright owner for inclusion in Edecan.
Private credentials, databases, brand records, deployment configuration,
generated builds, dependency trees and Git history are not included.

The native desktop bundle aggregates separate third-party executables that are
not relicensed under this package's Apache-2.0 license:

- ffmpeg and ffprobe 8.1.2 are separate GPL-3.0-or-later programs. macOS builds
  come from https://ffmpeg.martin-riedl.de; Linux and Windows builds come from
  https://github.com/BtbN/FFmpeg-Builds. The installer rejects builds
  marked nonfree or unredistributable. Full GPL text, build configuration and
  exact binary/source metadata are retained under tools/licenses in the native
  resource. Corresponding FFmpeg source is at
  https://github.com/FFmpeg/FFmpeg/tree/n8.1.2.
- yt-dlp 2026.06.09 (https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp) is a separate program.
  Its source is under the Unlicense; the distributed PyInstaller executable is
  GPLv3+ because it bundles third-party components. The full Unlicense,
  THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES and GPL text are retained under tools/licenses.

Those programs remain separate executables invoked through configured paths.
Their own license terms apply to them.
